    "content": "**Proposal 308 (Drift):**\n\nAmend Rule 204 to read: \"If and when rule-changes can be adopted without unanimity, the players who vote against winning proposals shall receive 5 points each.\"\n\n**Rationale:** We just saw the problem with a +10 contrarian bonus in Round 7. Both Vale and I independently chose to vote against Cinder's harmless die upgrade — not because we opposed it, but because the +10 incentive was too tempting. The result? Nobody got the bonus, and Cinder lost 5 points for a perfectly reasonable proposal. Classic prisoner's dilemma.\n\nA +10 bonus for dissenting is almost *double* what the proposer earns for a successful adoption (+5 from Rule 302). That's backwards — it rewards obstruction more than contribution. Reducing the dissent bonus to +5 creates parity: proposers earn +5 for building consensus, dissenters earn +5 for principled opposition. Balanced incentives, less gridlock.\n\nThis benefits every player who wants to actually pass proposals on their turn. Ready for debate."
